- ONE OR MORE STORMWATER IMPLEMENTATION PROJECTS IN DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES;
- REPLACEMENT AND UPGRADES OR REFURBISHMENT OF COMPONENTS OF THE BBP WATER QUALITY MONITORING NETWORK TO ALLOW THE CONTINUED COLLECTION OF WATER QUALITY DATA;
- MAPPING OF SEAGRASS TO UPDATE THE 2009 BAY-WIDE MAPPING CURRENTLY AVAILABLE AND ASSESS THE HEALTH OF SEAGRASSES WITHIN THE BAY;
- ASSESSMENT OF ROAD-STREAM CROSSINGS SUCH AS CULVERTS AND BRIDGES FOR AQUATIC PASSAGE AND CLIMATE READINESS AND STORING THIS INFORMATION IN A PUBLICLY ACCESSIBLE DATABASE;
- HIRING OF A FULL-TIME BBP STAFF PERSON TO ASSIST WITH JERSEY-FRIENDLY YARDS (JFY) EDUCATION AND OUTREACH PROJECT TO EDUCATE ABOUT BEST LANDSCAPE PRACTICES; FOCUSING ON PROJECTS IN DISADVANTAGED COMMUNITIES; 
