DESCRIPTION:THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT IS PROVIDED TO MASSACHUSETTS EXECUTIVE OFFICE OF ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL AFFAIRS (MA EOEEA) TO SUPPORT IMPLEMENTATION OF THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) COMPREHENSIVE CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT PLAN (CCMP). THE GOAL IS TO RESTORE AND MAINTAIN THE CHEMICAL, PHYSICAL, AND BIOLOGICAL INTEGRITY OF THE ESTUARY AND SUPPORT ITS SUSTAINABLE HUMAN USES THROUGH TASKS OUTLINED IN ANNUAL WORKPLANS OF THE BBNEP AND ITS PARTNERS. THE COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT SUPPORTS ACTIVITIES THAT WILL REMEDIATE AND RESTORE WETLANDS, LESSEN POLLUTION FROM STORMWATER AND WASTEWATER, AND HELP COMMUNITIES WITH OPEN SPACE AND NATURAL RESOURCE PLANNING AND PROTECTION.ACTIVITIES:THE WORKPLAN FOR THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) INCLUDES THE FOLLOWING ACTIVITIES THAT WILL HELP MEET THE GOALS OF THE COMPREHENSIVE CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT PLAN (CCMP):
- WETLAND RESTORATION AND OPEN SPACE PROTECTION AND RESTORATION;
- STORMWATER REMEDIATION AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE;
- MUNICIPAL GRANT PROGRAM;
- CITIZEN WATER QUALITY MONITORING;
- ENVIRONMENTAL INDICATORS AND OUTCOMES TRACKING;
- OUTREACH AND EDUCATION;
- SALT MARSH LOSS ASSESSMENT AND RUNNEL STUDY;
- TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO SUPPORT COASTAL RESILIENCY AND MUNICIPAL VULNERABILITY PREPAREDNESS; AND
- CCMP UPDATE.
SUBRECIPIENT:THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) IS PROPOSING THE FOLLOWING SUBAWARDS:
- BUZZARDS BAY COALITION (BBC) MONITORING;
- SEA LAB SUPPORT;
- UNIVERSITY OF MASSACHUSETTS (UMASS) SALT MARSH UNMANNED AERIAL VEHICLE (UAV) STUDY;
- WOODWELL CLIMATE RESEARCH CENTER RIVER MONITORING PROGRAM;
- BBC AND MARINE BIOLOGICAL LABORATORY (MBL) RED BROOK BENTHIC FLUX SAMPLING; AND
- MUNICIPAL GRANT PROGRAMOUTCOMES:THE GOAL OF THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT TO THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) IS TO IMPLEMENT THEIR COMPREHENSIVE CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT PLAN (CCMP). THE GOAL IS TO RESTORE AND MAINTAIN THE CHEMICAL, PHYSICAL, AND BIOLOGICAL INTEGRITY OF THE ESTUARY AND SUPPORT ITS SUSTAINABLE HUMAN USES. ANTICIPATED OUTCOMES AND DELIVERABLES INCLUDE:
- THE PERMANENT PROTECTION OF OPEN SPACE THROUGHOUT BUZZARDS BAY;
- ANNUAL REPORTING OF WETLAND AND HABITAT ACRES PROTECTED OR RESTORED;
- STORMWATER ENGINEERING DESIGNS FOR PRIORITY SITES;
- SHELLFISH BED CLOSURE MAPS FOR BUZZARDS BAY;
- REPORT ON THE HISTORY OF WASTEWATER LOADING TO BUZZARDS BAY;
- REPORT ON HISTORY OF SALT MARSH BOUNDARY CHANGES; AND
- UPDATED CCMP.

INTENDED BENEFICIARIES OF THE BBNEP INCLUDE:
- RESIDENTS OF ACUSHNET, BOURNE, DARTMOUTH, FAIRHAVEN, FALMOUTH, GOSNOLD, MARION, MATTAPOISETT, NEW BEDFORD, ROCHESTER, WAREHAM, AND WESTPORT;
- THE SOUTHEAST NEW ENGLAND PROGRAM (SNEP) REGION;
- THE GENERAL PUBLIC IN BUZZARDS BAY WATERSHED STUDY AREA; AND
- THE ECOSYSTEMS AND ECOSYSTEM SERVICES OF BUZZARDS BAY.

DESCRIPTION:THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT IS PROVIDED TO MASSACHUSETTS EXECUTIVE OFFICE OF ENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL AFFAIRS (MA EOEEA) TO SUPPORT THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE BIPARTISAN INFRASTRUCTURE LAW (BIL) THROUGH THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) COMPREHENSIVE CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT PLAN (CCMP). THE GOAL IS TO RESTORE AND MAINTAIN THE CHEMICAL, PHYSICAL, AND BIOLOGICAL INTEGRITY OF THE ESTUARY AND SUPPORT ITS SUSTAINABLE HUMAN USES THROUGH TASKS OUTLINED IN THE BIL WORKPLAN OF BBNEP AND ITS PARTNERS. THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT WILL SUPPORT THE ONGOING BUZZARDS BAY STORMWATER COLLABORATIVE, PROVIDE SUBAWARDS THROUGH A MUNICIPAL GRANT PROGRAM TO SUPPORT MUNICIPAL INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS, AND PROVIDE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO MUNICIPALITIES DEVELOPING INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS.ACTIVITIES:THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) WILL UTILIZE BIPARTISAN INFRASTRUCTURE LAW (BIL) FUNDS TO SUPPORT ITS COMPREHENSIVE CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT PLAN (CCMP). THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT WILL SUPPORT THE BUZZARDS BAY STORMWATER COLLABORATIVE, PROVIDE SUBAWARDS TO SUPPORT MUNICIPAL INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS, AND PROVIDE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO MUNICIPALITIES DEVELOPING INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS.SUBRECIPIENT:BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) WILL IMPLEMENT THEIR COMPREHENSIVE CONSERVATION AND MANAGEMENT PLAN (CCMP) BY PROVIDING SUBAWARDS TO SUPPORT TASKS OUTLINED IN THE BIPARTISAN INFRASTRUCTURE LAW (BIL) WORKPLAN OF BBNEP AND ITS PARTNERS. THE SUBAWARDS ARE:
- SUPPORTING THE BUZZARDS BAY STORMWATER COLLABORATIVE;
- A MUNICIPAL INFRASTRUCTURE SUPPORT GRANT PROGRAM WITH ELIGIBLE PRODUCTS INCLUDING:
     - STORMWATER REMEDIATION DESIGNS;
     - IMPLEMENTATION AND CONSTRUCTION OF EXISTING STORMWATER DESIGNS;
     - SUPPORT FOR TASKS TO ACHIEVE MS4 COMPLIANCE;
     - FEASIBILITY STUDIES AND CONCEPTUAL PLANS TO ENHANCE NITROGEN REMOVAL FROM MUNICIPAL WASTEWATER TREATMENT FACILITIES;
     - WETLAND, HABITAT, AND MIGRATORY FISH PASSAGE RESTORATION;
     - CONSTRUCTION OF BOAT PUMP-OUT FACILITIES;
     - TRACKING OPERATION, MAINTENANCE, AND MONITORING OF INNOVATIVE AND ALTERNATIVE SEPTIC SYSTEMS;
     - OTHER BIL-ELIGIBLE PROJECTS THAT RESTORE COASTAL WATERS AND SUPPORT THE BBNEP CCMP;OUTCOMES:THE BUZZARDS BAY NATIONAL ESTUARY PROGRAM (BBNEP) WILL OVERSEE AND GUIDE THE BUZZARDS BAY STORMWATER COLLABORATIVE STORMWATER NETWORK MAPPING AND DISCHARGE MONITORING PROGRAM AND WATER QUALITY DATABASE, AS WELL AS DEVELOPING STORMWATER INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS AND PROPOSALS THROUGHOUT BUZZARDS BAY, INCLUDING ENVIRONMENTAL JUSTICE COMMUNITIES. BBNEP WILL ALSO RELEASE A REQUEST FOR PROPOSALS FOR A MUNICIPAL GRANT PROGRAM FOR STORMWATER REMEDIATION DESIGNS, IMPLEMENTATION AND CONSTRUCTION OF EXISTING STORMWATER DESIGNS, ENHANCED NITROGEN REMOVAL PLANS, FISH PASSAGE RESTORATION, AND OTHER PROJECTS THAT MITIGATE OR RESTORE COASTAL WATERS. BBNEP WILL ALSO PROVIDE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO MUNICIPALITIES SEEKING TO UNDERTAKE INFRASTRUCTURE PROJECTS IN THE BBNEP STUDY AREA.

DIRECT BENEFICIARIES OF THIS PROGRAM INCLUDE RESIDENTS OF THE BUZZARDS BAY WATERSHED STUDY AREA, AND THE ECOSYSTEM AND USERS OF ECOSYSTEM SERVICES.

